          {
            "question": "How do I know if my sewer line needs repair?",
            "answer": "Warning signs include frequent drain backups, sewage odors in your yard, unusually green patches of grass, soggy areas in your lawn, and gurgling sounds from toilets or drains."
          },
          {
            "question": "What is trenchless sewer repair?",
            "answer": "Trenchless repair is a minimally invasive method that fixes sewer lines without digging up your yard. Techniques include pipe lining and <a href='/specialty/sewer-line-services/pipe-bursting-lining'><strong>pipe bursting</strong></a>, which are faster and less disruptive."
          },
          {
            "question": "How long does a sewer line replacement take?",
            "answer": "A traditional sewer line replacement typically takes 1-3 days depending on the length and depth. Trenchless methods can often be completed in a single day with minimal disruption."
          }
        ]
